at theJapanese Embassy.

735
01:28:22,124 --> 01:28:25,042
TheJapanese were the only people
prepared to help me.

736
01:28:25,127 --> 01:28:27,128
Help you for nothing?

737
01:28:28,839 --> 01:28:32,758
Japan has an emperor.
We are almost the same age.

738
01:28:32,843 --> 01:28:35,970
I thought it was kindness.

739
01:28:36,054 --> 01:28:40,516
At the same time I realized that,
for many Chinese, I was an alien...

740
01:28:40,600 --> 01:28:43,853
simply because I am Manchurian.

741
01:28:43,937 --> 01:28:49,150
There was even an anti-Manchurian league
who wanted to assassinate me.

742
01:28:49,234 --> 01:28:52,236
So I went to live in Tientsin.

743
01:28:53,864 --> 01:28:58,826
It was a nice, provincial town
with a big port.

744
01:28:58,910 --> 01:29:02,580
In those days they had
a large international settlement

745
01:29:02,664 --> 01:29:05,458
TheJapanese thought
it would be safer for me there

746
01:29:05,542 --> 01:29:08,294
were theJapanese
paying foryou in Tientsin?

747
01:29:08,378 --> 01:29:10,296
oh, no.

748
01:29:10,380 --> 01:29:13,716
I had to rent a villa —
the Villa Chang.

749
01:29:13,800 --> 01:29:16,010
And it was very expensive.

750
01:29:16,094 --> 01:29:18,262
So were the bodyguards.

751
01:29:19,264 --> 01:29:21,766
I spent a lot of money in Tientsin

752
01:29:21,850 --> 01:29:25,936
Did you still believe
in a restoration ofthe imperial system?

753
01:29:26,021 --> 01:29:29,190
others did.
The little court in exile

754
01:29:30,692 --> 01:29:34,278
I cannot remember how much jade
and jewelry they made me spend...

755
01:29:34,363 --> 01:29:39,325
to buy the friendship ofsome warlord
or some White Russian general.

756
01:29:39,409 --> 01:29:41,243
What else
did you spend your money on?

757
01:29:41,328 --> 01:29:46,040
I was never tired
of buying pianos, watches, radios.

758
01:29:46,124 --> 01:29:48,417
As long as they were foreign

759
01:29:48,502 --> 01:29:50,419
ofcourse.

760
01:29:50,504 --> 01:29:52,630
Anything western was good.

761
01:29:52,714 --> 01:29:56,926
Especially Wrigley's Chewing Gum,
Bayer Aspirin, and cars.

762
01:29:57,010 --> 01:29:59,345
